==Style of play==
Milner has a positive and unselfish attitude towards his teammates.<ref name="team"/> As a result he is not a prolific goal scorer, but does produce a high number of assists. He has also expressed willingness to play as much as possible, saying that he is "bored" when not playing.<ref>{{cite web
|url = http://icnewcastle.icnetwork.co.uk/newcastleunited/journalsport/tm_method=full%26objectid=19609527%26siteid=50081-name_page.html
|title = FOOTBALL THE PREMIERSHIP INTERVIEW: One to watch in 2006: 'Players 
|work=icnetwork
|date = [[2007-08-11]]
|accessdate = 2007-08-13}}</ref> He has the ability to pass and shoot with both feet. However he describes defending as one of his weaknesses and therefore usually goes forward for [[Set piece (football)|set pieces]] and is often a candidate to take [[Corner kick|corners]] or [[Direct free kick|free kicks]].<ref name="interview">{{cite web
  | title = The boy's a bit special - James Milner
  | publisher = fourfourtwo
  | url = http://www.fourfourtwo.premiumtv.co.uk/page/TheBoys/0,,11442~607366,00.html
  | accessdate = 2007-07-29 }}</ref> This is supported by the fact he can produce accurate [[Cross (football)|crosses]] and is able to play on either side of the field. He has been described as being "a good reader of the game".<ref name="sky sports">{{cite web
  | title = Opta Jury: James Milner
  | publisher = Sky Sports
  | date = 2006-09-28
  | url = http://home.skysports.com/column.aspx?hlid=291306&lid=jury&title=Opta+Jury:+James+Milner&channel=skysports_home_page
  | accessdate = 2007-07-29 }}</ref>
{{Quote_box|
 width=30%
|align=left
|quote=All my life I've wanted to do what I'm doing now. Now I'm here, and enjoying every minute of it. You've got to make a few sacrifices, but I don't mind that.
|source=&ndash;James Milner<ref name="findarticles2"/>
|}}
He is regarded as a player with a fair amount of pace and for this reason his main role on the team is as a wide midfielder, creating scoring opportunities as well as taking the ball past defenders. His awareness of players around him and his willingness to pass has been described as mature for a player of his age,<ref name="Chelsea"/> which allows him to pick out a forward run being made by a teammate from a range of positions on the field. His awareness has also given him the confidence to take on defenders. Milner has a good discipline record, having never been sent off and [[Misconduct (football)|booked]] 15 times in his career.<ref name="stats"/><ref name="footballanorak">{{cite web
  | title = James Milner News and Statistics
  | publisher = footballanorak
  | url = http://www.footballanorak.com/James-Milner-pid-670.html
  | accessdate = 2007-07-31 }}</ref> His teammate [[Nolberto Solano]] said that his emergence would be important to the team because of his pace.<ref>{{cite web
  | title = Sol hails return of young gun Milner
  | publisher = officialplayersites
  | url = http://www.officialplayersites.com/players/solano/article.php?id=815
  | date = 2006-07-14
  | accessdate = 2007-07-29 }}</ref> His work ethic in training has been compared to that of [[Frank Lampard|Frank Lampard's]].<ref name="Lampard"/> Sky Sports.com gave him an overall rating of 6.3 out of 10.<ref>{{cite web
  | title = James Milner
  | publisher = Sky Sports
  | url = http://www.skysports.com/football/player/0,,11678_247364,00.html
  | accessdate = 2007-08-11 }}</ref>

