==Off the pitch==
Milner has always expressed praise for his team&ndash;mates and managers and has never been reported to have said anything controversial or been involved in any controversial incidents<!-- NOTE: Correct me if I'm wrong. --> and rarely speaks to the media about anything outside of football. He takes an easy-going and optimistic approach to football. He enjoys watching most other sports particularly [[cricket]] and [[golf]], he has a [[Golf handicap|handicap]] of 16. He displays maturity beyond that expected from someone of his age, he lives with his parents and sister. 

His nickname at Newcastle is "Machine Gun", after his teammates were impressed by his [[darts]] ability.<ref>{{cite web
  | last = Edwards 
  | first = Luke
  | title = Harper hits the bulls eye
  | publisher = icnetwork
  | date = 2007-02-24
  | url = http://icnewcastle.icnetwork.co.uk/newcastleunited/journalsport/tm_headline=harper-hits-the-bullseye&method=full&objectid=18669670&siteid=50081-name_page.html
  | accessdate = 2007-08-11 }}</ref> He also owns a [[PlayStation]], a [[BMW X3]], a pet [[Canaan Dog|Canaan hound]]. He sees himself as a funny person who is a hard-worker, confident and relaxed.<ref name="interview"/> He rarely drinks [[alcohol]] or goes on nights out.<ref name="findarticles2"/>

